{
  "texts": [
    "However, most current AI models focus on unimodal data streams, limiting their capacity to replicate the complexity of human perception.",
    "Multimodal integration requires sophisticated data fusion techniques that align inputs with different temporal and spatial properties.",
    "For example, synchronizing olfactory sensor outputs with visual cues from food presentation is technically challenging but crucial for accurate flavor modeling.",
    "The lack of unified frameworks for multimodal data representation and learning further impedes progress in this area.",
    "Standardization remains a persistent issue across the field."
  ]
}